Vice President Biden met with a delegation from Southern Sudan to discuss the upcoming referendum on Southern self-determination. He expressed the US commitment to a peaceful outcome and offered political, financial, and technical support. He also emphasized the need to strengthen state institutions and governance in the South. Biden encouraged negotiations with Khartoum on post-referendum arrangements, including border demarcation, revenue sharing, and citizenship rights. Additionally, he pledged continued US assistance to the Sudan People's Liberation Army. In a separate meeting, Biden discussed steps to help Somalia achieve stability with UN and African Union representatives. He highlighted the challenges faced by AMISOM and the need for political inclusivity and stability in the Transitional Federal Government.